Program: Discovery
Title: Parkinson's Disease
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxj7
Last Broadcast Date: 27 October 1999
The experience of suffering from Parkinson's Disease. The programme speaks to those who have the degenerative disease which causes tremors and is incurable. It is caused by lack of dopamine, however there is hope following the success of clinical trials of new treatments.